This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for facial expression recognition, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning models and feature extraction techniques also suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the creation of a novel dataset, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC) categories.
